34// This is a helper class for JSReceiver::GetKeys which collects and sorts keys.
35// GetKeys needs to sort keys per prototype level, first showing the integer
36// indices from elements then the strings from the properties. However, this
37// does not apply to proxies which are in full control of how the keys are
38// sorted.
39//
40// For performance reasons the KeyAccumulator internally separates integer keys
41// in |elements_| into sorted lists per prototype level. String keys are
42// collected in |string_properties_|, a single OrderedHashSet (similar for
43// Symbols in |symbol_properties_|. To separate the keys per level later when
44// assembling the final list, |levelLengths_| keeps track of the number of
45// String and Symbol keys per level.
46//
47// Only unique keys are kept by the KeyAccumulator, strings are stored in a
48// HashSet for inexpensive lookups. Integer keys are kept in sorted lists which
49// are more compact and allow for reasonably fast includes check.
50class KeyAccumulator final {
51 public:
52 KeyAccumulator(Isolate* isolate, KeyCollectionMode mode,
53 PropertyFilter filter)
54 : isolate_(isolate), mode_(mode), filter_(filter) {}
55 ~KeyAccumulator() = default;
56 KeyAccumulator(const KeyAccumulator&) = delete;
57 KeyAccumulator& operator=(const KeyAccumulator&) = delete;
58
59 static MaybeHandle<FixedArray> GetKeys(
60 Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSReceiver> object, KeyCollectionMode mode,
61 PropertyFilter filter,
62 GetKeysConversion keys_conversion = GetKeysConversion::kKeepNumbers,
63 bool is_for_in = false, bool skip_indices = false);
64
65 Handle<FixedArray> GetKeys(
66 GetKeysConversion convert = GetKeysConversion::kKeepNumbers);
67 Maybe<bool> CollectKeys(Handle<JSReceiver> receiver,
68 Handle<JSReceiver> object);
69
70 // Might return directly the object's enum_cache, copy the result before using
71 // as an elements backing store for a JSObject.
72 // Does not throw for uninitialized exports in module namespace objects, so
73 // this has to be checked separately.
74 static Handle<FixedArray> GetOwnEnumPropertyKeys(Isolate* isolate,
75 Handle<JSObject> object);
76
77 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT ExceptionStatus
78 AddKey(Tagged<Object> key, AddKeyConversion convert = DO_NOT_CONVERT);
79 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT ExceptionStatus
80 AddKey(Handle<Object> key, AddKeyConversion convert = DO_NOT_CONVERT);
81
82 // Jump to the next level, pushing the current |levelLength_| to
83 // |levelLengths_| and adding a new list to |elements_|.
84 Isolate* isolate() { return isolate_; }
85 // Filter keys based on their property descriptors.
86 PropertyFilter filter() { return filter_; }
87 // The collection mode defines whether we collect the keys from the prototype
88 // chain or only look at the receiver.
89 KeyCollectionMode mode() { return mode_; }
90 void set_skip_indices(bool value) { skip_indices_ = value; }
91 // Shadowing keys are used to filter keys. This happens when non-enumerable
92 // keys appear again on the prototype chain.
93 void AddShadowingKey(Tagged<Object> key, AllowGarbageCollection* allow_gc);
94 void AddShadowingKey(Handle<Object> key);
95
96 private:
97 enum IndexedOrNamed { kIndexed, kNamed };

177// The FastKeyAccumulator handles the cases where there are no elements on the
178// prototype chain and forwards the complex/slow cases to the normal
179// KeyAccumulator. This significantly speeds up the cases where the OWN_ONLY
180// case where we do not have to walk the prototype chain.
181class FastKeyAccumulator {
182 public:
183 FastKeyAccumulator(Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSReceiver> receiver,
184 KeyCollectionMode mode, PropertyFilter filter,
185 bool is_for_in = false, bool skip_indices = false)
186 : isolate_(isolate),
187 receiver_(receiver),
188 mode_(mode),
189 filter_(filter),
190 is_for_in_(is_for_in),
191 skip_indices_(skip_indices) {
192 Prepare();
193 }
194 FastKeyAccumulator(const FastKeyAccumulator&) = delete;
195 FastKeyAccumulator& operator=(const FastKeyAccumulator&) = delete;
196
197 bool is_receiver_simple_enum() { return is_receiver_simple_enum_; }
198 bool has_empty_prototype() { return has_empty_prototype_; }
199 bool may_have_elements() { return may_have_elements_; }
200
201 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> GetKeys(
202 GetKeysConversion convert = GetKeysConversion::kKeepNumbers);
203
204 // Initialize the the enum cache for a map with all of the following:
205 // - uninitialized enum length
206 // - fast properties (i.e. !is_dictionary_map())
207 // - has >0 enumerable own properties
208 //
209 // The number of enumerable properties is passed in as an optimization, for
210 // when the caller has already computed it.
211 //
212 // Returns the keys.
213 static Handle<FixedArray> InitializeFastPropertyEnumCache(
214 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Map> map, int enum_length,
215 AllocationType allocation = AllocationType::kOld);
216
217 private:
218 void Prepare();
219 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> GetKeysFast(GetKeysConversion convert);
220 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> GetKeysSlow(GetKeysConversion convert);
221 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> GetKeysWithPrototypeInfoCache(
222 GetKeysConversion convert);
223
224 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> GetOwnKeysWithUninitializedEnumLength();
225
226 bool MayHaveElements(Tagged<JSReceiver> receiver);
227 bool TryPrototypeInfoCache(Handle<JSReceiver> receiver);
228
229 Isolate* isolate_;
230 Handle<JSReceiver> receiver_;
231 Handle<Map> first_prototype_map_;
232 Handle<JSReceiver> first_prototype_;
233 Handle<JSReceiver> last_non_empty_prototype_;
234 KeyCollectionMode mode_;
235 PropertyFilter filter_;
236 bool is_for_in_ = false;
237 bool skip_indices_ = false;
238 bool is_receiver_simple_enum_ = false;
239 bool has_empty_prototype_ = false;
240 bool may_have_elements_ = true;
241 bool has_prototype_info_cache_ = false;
242 bool try_prototype_info_cache_ = false;
243 bool only_own_has_simple_elements_ = false;
244};
